You have the complete CAPO package. I Purchased the complete series way back, I thought this would be the conclusion, since the last chapter is basically left open for an extra season, and this package, titled El Capo El Final, makes you think that this is going to show what happens after they catch the Capo in the last chapter, because it is not clear what happened to him in the end. So if you have the Complete EL CAPO, don't waste your money, you will be watching the second part of El Capo again, from the chapter where the Police chases them when they are hiding in the cave.

The good news: This was the second half of El Capo, every single episode unedited. The entire series had 90 episodes, and this is the second half.  The price is very cheap. The acting is excellent, the story is fascinating, and there are lots of characters.  The bad news: There are no subtitles and the slang and accents are a bit hard to understand unless you're a native speaker, or have practiced Spanish a lot.  Also, I didn't completely agree with the way the story portrays various characters as either good, or worthy of redemption, when I thought they were horrible.
